@import ./_tui.convo

> user
Refine layout sizing for grid rows and flex edge cases.

Goals:
- Review and improve natural sizing for row, column, and grid layouts.
- Handle flex distribution edge cases more predictably.
- Avoid division by zero when total flex is zero.
- Improve grid row height calculations when constrained width is available.
- Keep the existing layout model intact.

Acceptance criteria:
- Row and column layouts handle all-flex, no-flex, and mixed children predictably.
- Grid layout handles fixed `cr` columns and flexible `fr` columns predictably.
- Grid row heights are calculated from constrained child widths.
- Layout code avoids negative sizes and divide-by-zero behavior.
- Existing TUI screens render the same or better.

Update notes at the end of your response
